WEBVTT

00:25.400 --> 00:26.777
Here, let me help.

00:35.410 --> 00:36.411
Here you go.

01:01.728 --> 01:02.729
(CLICKS TONGUE) Come on.

01:13.490 --> 01:16.326
I wish we had more to show for our trip,

01:16.410 --> 01:18.370
with all the new mouths to feed, too.

01:18.912 --> 01:21.290
We'll make it work. We always do.

01:23.792 --> 01:25.210
You're not coming back with me?

01:27.171 --> 01:29.965
I'm gonna stay
a little while longer. Keep looking.

01:35.137 --> 01:37.848
You want a ride?
Bike's just a little further.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.141
No, I'm good.

01:50.611 --> 01:52.696
-Hey, um...
-You don't have to apologize.

01:52.779 --> 01:53.822
I'm good, really.

01:56.241 --> 01:57.826
I was just gonna say good luck.

02:01.747 --> 02:02.789
(CLICKS TONGUE)

02:05.167 --> 02:07.211
-Good luck to you, too.
-Thanks.

02:23.101 --> 02:24.144
Nice.

02:29.483 --> 02:31.485
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

04:14.254 --> 04:15.797
Come on, boy. Let's get you home.

04:31.104 --> 04:34.566
All right. In you go.
Hmm. Smells like Daryl.

04:51.375 --> 04:52.501
Can you lay down?

05:01.635 --> 05:02.636
(SIGHS)

05:06.014 --> 05:07.641
For the record...

05:10.269 --> 05:12.396
I didn't need an apology from him.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.942
I know he meant what he said.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.863
We don't need apologies, just a truce.

05:22.698 --> 05:24.199
Doesn't fix anything.

05:26.952 --> 05:28.078
You know.

05:28.203 --> 05:29.621
(DOG WHINING)

05:29.705 --> 05:33.625
Belly rubs, too. Yes, belly rubs, too.

05:40.465 --> 05:42.801
I was thinking I'd work
on the North Gate post today,

05:42.885 --> 05:45.137
and if things work out,
I would may be get into, uh,

05:45.220 --> 05:47.055
cleaning the dead fish out of the fishery.

05:50.392 --> 05:52.603
-Hey, dude.
-Hi, Jerry.

05:53.437 --> 05:55.564
Rosita's already got a crew
working on the guard post

05:55.647 --> 05:57.691
and the fishery got cleaned up
while you were out.

05:58.108 --> 05:59.443
Doesn't smell like it.

05:59.818 --> 06:01.904
Stinky fish make killer fertilizer.

06:02.487 --> 06:03.822
How was your trip with Daryl?

06:04.323 --> 06:06.700
Fine. What about you? You need help?

06:07.826 --> 06:10.329
Nah, I got it. I'm sure
there are better uses of your time.

06:11.246 --> 06:12.372
Yeah.

06:12.998 --> 06:14.166
Yeah, I'll figure something out.

06:14.583 --> 06:15.751
What's that you got there?

06:17.085 --> 06:20.839
Oh, this...
Uh, I just found it in the street.

06:21.882 --> 06:24.259
Somebody must have dropped it
during the evacuation.

06:25.219 --> 06:26.762
-Okay.
-I don't know.

06:27.012 --> 06:28.972
I thought I'd try
to get the stains out of it.

06:29.056 --> 06:32.017
Maybe mend this little... rip.

06:33.644 --> 06:34.978
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)
I don't know.

06:36.271 --> 06:39.191
I don't know, somebody loved it
and I just want to fix something.

06:39.691 --> 06:40.776
Why not?

06:41.318 --> 06:42.736
Yeah, sure.

06:45.364 --> 06:46.448
Jerry.

06:48.367 --> 06:50.244
Tell me how I can help out, please.

06:50.619 --> 06:52.329
Anything. Anything at all.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.665
Okay... Okay.

06:56.291 --> 06:57.334
Thinking.

06:59.795 --> 07:01.547
I think food is important to thinking.

07:03.966 --> 07:05.050
Great.

07:05.676 --> 07:08.136
I'm sure I can whip up something
from what I found.

07:08.345 --> 07:09.596
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

07:10.264 --> 07:11.473
Thanks, Jerry.

07:11.723 --> 07:13.642
One thing. A bunch of Maggie's people

07:13.725 --> 07:15.310
are crashed in Michonne's kitchen.

07:15.394 --> 07:16.562
-So...
-Not a problem.

07:16.895 --> 07:18.355
There's a hot pot in the pantry.

07:19.273 --> 07:20.399
JERRY: Uh, yeah, I forgot.

07:20.482 --> 07:23.110
The solar panels are all messed up.

07:23.193 --> 07:26.655
So... Whisperers, probably. So no juice.

07:27.948 --> 07:31.201
And we had to throw out a bunch of grain.

07:32.244 --> 07:33.871
-Why's that?
-Rats.

07:36.123 --> 07:38.292
-Anything else?
-What you gonna make?

07:38.375 --> 07:40.544
I don't know, maybe some soup.

07:40.669 --> 07:41.753
(SOFTLY) Ah.

07:41.837 --> 07:42.880
Yeah.

07:43.172 --> 07:47.801
Got a couple of fish, some nuts
and mushrooms. I'll make it work.

07:48.594 --> 07:49.720
You always do.

07:56.143 --> 07:57.686
Did you ever hear the story of Stone Soup?

07:59.521 --> 08:01.440
Yeah, they used to teach it
to us in school.

08:02.274 --> 08:04.193
There was this hungry stranger
that came to a village.

08:04.276 --> 08:07.613
But he didn't have anything to trade
for food except for a big rock.

08:09.323 --> 08:13.160
So he convinced all the villagers
to try his world-famous Stone Soup.

08:13.869 --> 08:16.205
But before that, he tells one person,

08:16.538 --> 08:18.498
"Hey, I'm gonna have to borrow some salt."

08:18.916 --> 08:20.292
Then he tells another person,

08:20.417 --> 08:21.877
"Just gonna need a little bit of onion."

08:22.377 --> 08:23.378
Little by little,

08:23.462 --> 08:24.922
little bit of this, little bit of that

08:25.631 --> 08:26.924
from everyone in the village

08:28.300 --> 08:29.801
until he has a real soup.

08:31.220 --> 08:32.513
And everyone's happy.

08:34.806 --> 08:36.141
Doesn't sound very tasty.

08:37.392 --> 08:39.853
Maybe Ezekiel and the others
will bring help soon,

08:40.729 --> 08:42.523
and you won't have to make
a soup out of rocks.

08:43.982 --> 08:45.234
I hope so, too.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.324
This can be saved.

09:18.851 --> 09:20.060
(ENGINE CUTS)

09:25.274 --> 09:26.567
(ENGINE HISSING)

10:42.392 --> 10:43.560
(CRASHING)

10:44.561 --> 10:45.729
(DOG BARKING)

10:47.439 --> 10:48.482
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

10:55.322 --> 10:58.075
-(GROWLING)
-Hey! Hey! Hey!

11:02.412 --> 11:04.581
(EXCLAIMING) Stop that!

11:19.179 --> 11:20.389
Look at this mess.

11:25.894 --> 11:26.937
Back off!

11:27.396 --> 11:28.480
-(WHIMPERS)
-Back off!

11:29.648 --> 11:30.774
You take it easy.

11:32.693 --> 11:34.069
(SIGHS) Oh, man.

11:45.831 --> 11:46.915
Hmm.

11:53.505 --> 11:54.590
(DOG WHINING)

11:54.756 --> 11:57.634
I know. It's okay, buddy. It's just a rat.

11:59.595 --> 12:01.805
I know, I hear it, too.
I hear it, too.

12:02.347 --> 12:06.268
Hey, no, no. No!

12:06.810 --> 12:08.562
Dog! Dog, get back here.

12:09.897 --> 12:11.356
-(GROWLING)
-No, no!

12:11.440 --> 12:14.151
Bad dog. Bad dog. Go!

12:16.111 --> 12:17.321
Don't look at me like that.

12:17.863 --> 12:20.532
No, this is serious.
We need that food, go.

12:24.077 --> 12:25.078
Go.

12:30.000 --> 12:31.043
Damn it!

13:26.306 --> 13:28.475
See you later, asshole.

13:43.448 --> 13:44.449
How's that soup coming?

13:45.617 --> 13:46.785
Great, Great.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.328
Just need a couple more ingredients.

13:48.412 --> 13:50.873
Gonna go, see what I can rustle up
out there.

13:50.956 --> 13:52.416
You gonna rustle up some stones, too?

13:54.751 --> 13:55.919
Can't wait.

14:19.484 --> 14:21.069
(WALKERS GROWLING)

14:37.377 --> 14:38.420
What?

14:40.047 --> 14:42.174
Think I can't take you myself?

14:44.843 --> 14:46.053
First you...

14:49.348 --> 14:52.434
Then you and you and you
and you.

15:03.111 --> 15:04.279
(WALKERS GROWLING)

15:04.363 --> 15:05.572
(HACKING)

15:10.661 --> 15:12.538
CAROL: And where do you
think you're going?

15:24.842 --> 15:26.009
(HUMMING)

17:33.178 --> 17:34.429
(RUMBLING)

17:35.931 --> 17:36.932
Hey!

17:37.599 --> 17:39.017
Stop moving.

18:14.595 --> 18:15.721
Thanks, buddy.

18:21.602 --> 18:22.644
What the hell happened?

18:23.979 --> 18:25.063
Nothing.

18:25.814 --> 18:27.524
Got some nettles and dandelion greens.

18:27.608 --> 18:28.859
Tasty and nutritious.

18:29.902 --> 18:32.613
-You sure you're okay?
-Oh, yeah, back to it.

20:15.966 --> 20:17.009
You got it?

20:17.968 --> 20:19.011
I'm good.

20:19.970 --> 20:21.597
Cool. Cool.

20:22.639 --> 20:23.974
Let me know if you need anything.

20:25.017 --> 20:26.185
Sure will.

21:49.643 --> 21:50.853
(WALKERS GROWLING)

22:36.940 --> 22:38.192
(WALKERS GROWLING)

22:59.463 --> 23:00.464
(BRANCH SNAPS)

23:50.347 --> 23:51.849
(GRUNTING)

24:29.553 --> 24:30.637
Come on.

24:33.974 --> 24:35.267
(SIGHS) Come on.

24:38.812 --> 24:39.855
There we go.

24:39.938 --> 24:41.148
(WALKERS GROWLING)

24:53.243 --> 24:54.286
See you later, asshole.

25:30.864 --> 25:31.990
(WALKER GROWLS)

25:40.249 --> 25:41.917
You gotta be kidding me.

26:18.620 --> 26:19.663
Nice.

26:36.763 --> 26:38.640
Well, come on.

26:42.895 --> 26:44.521
Hey, don't make me beg.

26:46.064 --> 26:47.274
(KISSES)

26:47.357 --> 26:48.358
Good boy.

26:49.151 --> 26:51.195
There you go. Good boy.

26:54.656 --> 26:56.033
(HUMMING)

27:09.713 --> 27:13.342
You know, if you're a good boy,
I'll save you some scraps.

27:19.515 --> 27:20.516
(WHIMPERING)

27:33.070 --> 27:35.531
Got you, you little bastard.

27:36.990 --> 27:40.118
(SHRIEKS) No! No! No.

27:46.458 --> 27:47.543
Oh, no.

27:48.627 --> 27:49.920
Where are you?

27:54.716 --> 27:55.801
Damn it!

27:58.136 --> 27:59.263
(CAROL GROANS)

28:00.389 --> 28:02.057
No! No! No!

28:07.062 --> 28:08.063
There you are.

28:09.857 --> 28:11.275
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

28:17.364 --> 28:18.574
No. No.

28:19.324 --> 28:20.450
No!

28:22.828 --> 28:24.746
No! No, no. No.

28:25.664 --> 28:28.125
Shit. Shit. Shit.

28:40.262 --> 28:41.305
What?

28:42.014 --> 28:45.642
You two friends now?
This 'cause I yelled at you earlier?

28:59.823 --> 29:01.283
Screw it.

29:06.121 --> 29:10.250
Yeah, there'll be more sun tomorrow,
right, buddy?

29:14.630 --> 29:15.672
Come on.

29:33.524 --> 29:34.650
Come on.

29:43.242 --> 29:44.409
That's bold.

29:48.914 --> 29:51.416
You're lucky all the fight's
gone out of me.

29:59.883 --> 30:01.343
You miss him, don't you?

30:04.847 --> 30:05.931
Don't worry.

30:07.099 --> 30:08.225
He'll come back.

30:09.476 --> 30:10.894
He always comes back.

30:14.773 --> 30:16.358
I don't though. Do I?

30:17.609 --> 30:18.861
Yeah, I know.

30:22.823 --> 30:25.784
What do you think?
You think I should scram?

30:27.369 --> 30:29.121
Just get out of everybody's hair.

30:32.124 --> 30:33.208
I could.

30:35.961 --> 30:37.045
I could.

30:42.634 --> 30:46.013
Yeah, I miss him, too.

31:16.668 --> 31:18.337
(HOWLING)

31:35.521 --> 31:38.106
Cut it out. No. Cut it out.

31:47.324 --> 31:48.367
Hey.

32:06.677 --> 32:07.761
Come on.

32:10.722 --> 32:12.099
(ENGINE STARTS)

32:27.197 --> 32:28.907
(CAROL SHUSHING SOFTLY)

33:15.662 --> 33:17.039
(DOG WHINES)

33:45.692 --> 33:47.027
(RAT SQUEAKS)

35:08.859 --> 35:09.902
Damn it.

35:10.527 --> 35:11.695
(EXHALES)

35:37.471 --> 35:39.264
(WATER BOILING)

36:04.206 --> 36:05.791
(KNOCKING)

36:16.301 --> 36:17.427
Oh, hey.

36:19.388 --> 36:21.223
It's fine. I'm fixing it. What's up?

36:22.474 --> 36:25.227
The cover story was gonna be
that I was coming by for soup.

36:25.394 --> 36:27.437
But I'm not the best poker player.

36:28.397 --> 36:29.439
Poker?

36:29.648 --> 36:32.442
As in I have no poker face.

36:32.526 --> 36:36.613
So I'm just gonna fess up.
I'm just checking on you.

36:38.240 --> 36:39.616
You think I need checking on?

36:40.200 --> 36:42.953
I do. If Ezekiel were here,
he'd agree with me.

36:43.829 --> 36:45.122
I can't argue with that, then.

36:47.165 --> 36:48.709
Wish I can check in on him, too.

36:51.003 --> 36:52.880
Yeah, I'm sure he's on his way back here

36:52.963 --> 36:54.173
as fast as he can with the others.

36:54.423 --> 36:57.467
You know, probably just so he can
check in on people

36:57.551 --> 36:58.844
almost as much as you do.

36:59.761 --> 37:01.054
You know, it's pathological.

37:02.097 --> 37:05.517
Can't you just let
people like me suffer in peace?

37:06.351 --> 37:09.271
Yeah. Caring, it's a real problem.

37:13.609 --> 37:18.488
Yesterday wasn't my best day.

37:20.824 --> 37:21.867
It was a bad day.

37:26.413 --> 37:28.582
Is that why the wall in there
is all busted up?

37:31.210 --> 37:32.377
Guess so.

37:33.670 --> 37:36.465
You know, Ezekiel will have a saying
for this kind of thing.

37:37.382 --> 37:39.051
He has some good ones filed away.

37:40.010 --> 37:41.053
I know.

37:41.678 --> 37:43.055
Maybe I don't need a saying.

37:43.305 --> 37:45.265
May be I just need to fix what I broke.

37:46.391 --> 37:47.476
Here's one.

37:48.644 --> 37:50.687
"A friend is someone who thinks
you're perfect,

37:50.771 --> 37:52.814
"even if everyone else
thinks you're broken."

37:55.108 --> 37:57.653
I didn't even tell you
why I had a bad day yesterday.

37:57.861 --> 38:00.531
I just noticed that
Daryl didn't come back with you.

38:01.198 --> 38:02.741
Two plus two equals eureka, you know.

38:06.245 --> 38:07.829
What if you really are broken?

38:09.122 --> 38:12.543
What if your best friend
just realized it a whole lot later

38:12.626 --> 38:13.794
than everyone else did?

38:16.088 --> 38:18.549
Ezekiel probably has a saying
for that, too.

38:19.049 --> 38:20.717
I just don't know what it is.

38:22.427 --> 38:23.554
What would you say?

38:40.279 --> 38:44.867
-Was that...
-Yeah. Yeah.

38:48.996 --> 38:51.707
Why don't you come on in?
Soup's almost ready.

38:54.501 --> 38:58.755
<i>You made your bed</i>
<i>Now just sleep in it</i>

38:58.839 --> 39:01.300
<i>And dreams will cut the words out</i>

39:01.383 --> 39:05.804
<i>I grind my teeth</i>
<i>Grind my teeth to chalk</i>

39:05.888 --> 39:08.098
<i>Finding words to say to you</i>

39:15.439 --> 39:17.107
<i>Any fool</i>

39:17.191 --> 39:22.446
<i>Fool can carry on</i>
<i>with grand delusions</i>

39:22.613 --> 39:26.158
<i>Any dog</i>
<i>Dog like me could find</i>

39:26.241 --> 39:27.242
Sorry.

39:27.367 --> 39:29.453
<i>The best way through the fence</i>

39:29.536 --> 39:33.248
<i>You just donâ€™t think about the time</i>

39:36.627 --> 39:37.753
(CHUCKLES)

39:43.258 --> 39:44.343
What the hell happened to you?

39:44.801 --> 39:46.428
I was gonna ask you the same thing.

39:48.347 --> 39:49.848
You know, the usual.

39:51.683 --> 39:53.519
Yeah, same.

39:55.437 --> 39:58.023
-Find anything?
-Yeah, yeah.

39:59.983 --> 40:01.151
How was he? Was he good?

40:03.820 --> 40:04.988
He was.

40:07.449 --> 40:09.868
You hungry? I made some soup for everyone.

40:10.369 --> 40:12.538
No, I'm all right. Thank you though.

40:13.956 --> 40:15.123
Yeah, sure.

40:18.168 --> 40:19.461
Oh, um...

40:21.839 --> 40:23.298
Forgot to give this back to you.

40:25.217 --> 40:26.260
You can keep it.

40:27.511 --> 40:28.512
Really?

40:36.728 --> 40:40.065
I'm kinda beat.
I'm gonna hit the sack, all right?

40:40.983 --> 40:42.025
Yeah, me, too.

40:42.192 --> 40:43.485
Come on.

41:08.135 --> 41:10.137
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
